description: Thomas Valis finally realizes his destiny as a superhuman, while his brother Steven and his Mandroids meet their final fates, setting the stage for a new era of humanity!
name: The Power of One

description: On Earth, Steven Valis and his mutant Mandroids fight the devastating and final war, while on Mars, his brother Thomas searches for the nature of the mysterious beings who have chosen him to be the hope of humanity.
name: I Am Mars

description: Mankind continues its evolution as Steven Valis and his genetically engineered superior humans begin colonizing Mars. Meanwhile, Steven's brother Thomas learns about his emerging new powers.
name: Metamorphosis and Awakening

description: FRAZETTA! KIRBY! TOTH! MOEBIUS! KUBERT! MILLER! STEVENS! The BIG one! Literally: This gigantic 11 x 17 hardcover is the coffee table book of the Millennium! Nearly every great artist to ever work in comics is in this book which includes new stories from PETER BAGGE, KYLE BAKER, PHILIP BOND & PETER MILLIGAN, DARWYN COOKE, DAVE COOPER, DEAN HASPIEL, LOS BROS HERNANDEZ, ERIK LARSEN, DAVID MACK, PAT McKEOWN, BERNIE MIREAULT, MICHAEL AVON OEMING, PAUL POPE, ERIC POWELL, FRANK QUITELY, STEVEN T. SEAGLE & TEDDY KRISTIANSEN, JEFF SMITH, JAY STEPHENS, CRAIG THOMPSON, MATT WAGNER, JOE QUINONES & MARIS WICKS. Also MICHAEL ALLRED's latest - and most epic ever - MADMAN story! PLUS almost every Madman illustration collected over the past 20 years from all the greats. Surprises galore!

Tesana has never really fit into anything before but her daydreams. But an attempt to connect to her peers by joining in a pep rally committee leads her to discover a little white rabbit that lays bright colored eggs. Realizing that she may have found the real Easter Bunny, Tesana embarks on a journey to restore him to his natural habitat, to keep him safe from greedy hands!
name: GN

description: Collecting issues #1-3 and #5-7 of the red-hot new series that takes a fresh look at one of the most frightening horror icons of all time: Freddy Krueger! A new family has moved to the quiet town of Springwood and when night falls, the family quickly learns the town's horrible secret.
name: TPB

description:
Issue 33 of the Transformers Collectors' Club Magazine is arriving now and what an issue it is! This issue features an exclusive Q&A and look at the all-new Transformers Generations sub line, an interview with the man behind the voice of G1 Grimlock, Gregg Berger, part 3 of the 2010 series overview by Jim Sorenson, the final installment in the BotCon retrospective series and two all-new MTMTE profiles. All this and Part 3 of "The Coming Storm."

Contents

  • On the cover: Bio card art of BotCon 2010 Breakdown
  • Brian's Bytes and Bolts, From the Editor's Desk (inside cover)
  • "Gregg Berger - Almost 25 Years Later and STILL not a Bozo!" (p. 3) - Interview with Gregg Berger
  • HASBRO "GENERATIONS" INTERVIEW! (pp. 4-5) - Interview with Hasbro about Generations, including images of Darkmount, Red Alert, War for Cybertron Megatron and War for Cybertron Soundwave.
  • Profile: Onslaught (p. 6)
  • Profile: Moonracer (p. 7)
  • "Transformers: 2010 - part 3" by Jim Sorenson (p. 8) - Rodimus Prime and Galvatron's specific strategies for victory.
  • "THE GUESTS OF BOTCON" (p. 9) - BotCon has guests sometimes! Let's remind you.
  • "The Coming Storm: Part 3" - comic story (pp. 10-15)
  • Around Cybertron (Wings of Honor version), "Featured Fan Art!" with "Optimus Prime" by Audrey Cunningham, Liftor's profile (back cover)
name: The Coming Storm: Part 3
